President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate Ryan C. Crocker for a key administration post. Crocker is currently the Dean and Executive Professor at the George Bush School of Government and Public Service at Texas A&M University. He has had a distinguished career in the Foreign Service, serving as a U.S. Ambassador to Iraq, Pakistan, Syria, Kuwait, and Lebanon. He also served as the International Affairs Advisor at the National War College and played a significant role in reopening the American Embassy in Kabul, Afghanistan in 2002. Crocker has received numerous awards, including the Presidential Medal of Freedom, and holds a B.A. in English from Whitman College.